		<credit project="CfPBoK@https://slebok.github.io/cfpbok/"/>
		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2011"></a><br><code>sle2011/paper08</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2011</a> paper:</span><br><i>An Architecture for Information Exchange Based on Reference Models</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/HeikoPaulheim.html">Heiko Paulheim</a>, <a href="../profile/DanielOberle.html">Daniel Oberle</a>, <a href="../profile/RolandPlendl.html">Roland Plendl</a>, <a href="../profile/FlorianProbst.html">Florian Probst</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_9">10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_9</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagM">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> The core contribution is an integration architecture enabling information exchange across heterogeneous IT systems.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It relies on flexible bidirectional mappings between implementation models and a reference model.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3e.html"><span class="tagL">T3E: Ontologies</span></a><ul><li> The reference model is an ontology (ISO 15926 in OWL/RDF), making ontological modeling central to the approach.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6b.html"><span class="tagL">T6B: Industrial</span></a><ul><li> The feasibility is demonstrated in an industrial case study (SAP Research / Oil & Gas domain).
</li></ul></li></ul>
		<clear/>
